%N A226246 Triangle T(n, k), read by rows 1<=n, 1<=k<=n: Number of cells touched by a unit-width diagonal in a regular n X k grid.
%D A226246 J. D. E. Konhauser, D. J. Velleman and S. Wagon, Which Way Did the Bicycle Go?, Cambridge University Press, 1996, page 179.
%H A226246 Andrew Woods, <a href="/A226246/b226246.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..5050</a>
%F A226246 Let g := gcd(n,k), r := sqrt(n*n+k*k)/2.
%F A226246 T(n,k) = n+k+g+2*(g*floor(r/g)-floor(r/min(n,k))-1).
%e A226246 A paintbrush of unit width is dragged centrally along the diagonal of a rectangular 5 X 7 grid. The number of squares in the grid which contain paint in their interiors is T(5,7) = 19.
%Y A226246 The zero-width case is A199408 (or A074712).
